dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights; European possessions in Africa indicated by colors. On verso: 36. Africa. Map shows territory of Imperial British East Africa Company, established in 1887, later organized as British East Africa Protectorate in 1895; with adjoining "German sphere of influence." Probably issued in: Black's general atlas of the world. Edinburgh : Adam and Charles Black, [18--?] Historic Maps copy imperfect; lower right-hand portion of map wanting, with possible loss of imprint.
dct_publisher_sm: [Edinburgh? : Adam and Charles Black?, between 1887 and 1895]
